definition: to pay/to hand over (tax payment etc)
to hand in/to hand over/to seize
to pay/to hand over to/classifier for pairs or sets of things

sentences.english: Everyone agreed to kick in 50 cents for a present for the teacher.
sentences.chinese: 大家都同意每人繳付5角錢給老師買一件禮物。

sentences.english: The first installment of class fee after enrolment must be paid by cheque.
sentences.chinese: 獲取錄後，首次團費必須以支票繳付。

sentences.english: Ad valorem stamp duty is payable by the transferee(s) if this form is completed.
sentences.chinese: 如已填妥本表格，承讓人須繳付從價印花稅。

sentences.english: Applicants are required to pay a deposit of HK$100 per chip upon application.
sentences.chinese: 於報名時，每個晶片需繳付港幣100元之按金。

sentences.english: You’ll have to pay duty on this.
sentences.chinese: 你必須爲這項物品繳付稅金。

sentences.english: If a land to be used by a wholly foreign-owned enterprise has been developed, it shall pay the land development fee.
sentences.chinese: 外資企業使用經過開發的土地，應當繳付土地開發費。

sentences.english: Interest is payed weekly and you can't avoid it.
sentences.chinese: 你每週都要繳付貸款的利息，而且這是不能避免的。

sentences.english: The local gang forced all the residents in the neighbourhood to kick over 10 dollars a month.
sentences.chinese: 當地黑幫團伙迫使該街區內居民每月繳付10美元。

sentences.english: Hong Kong stamp duty is payable by the transferee(s) if this form is completed.
sentences.chinese: 填妥此表格後，承讓人須繳付香港印花稅。

sentences.english: ou'll have to pay duty on this.
sentences.chinese: 你必須爲這項物品繳付稅金。

sentences.english: Do you understand the nature of margined transactions?
sentences.chinese: 您瞭解以保證金形式繳付的交易嗎？

sentences.english: There might be handling clearing charges imposed by the bank.
sentences.chinese: 您或須繳付有關銀行手續結算費用。

sentences.english: Please pay the deposit along with the form to have your room reserved.
sentences.chinese: 使用本表申請者，須先繳付訂金，方得保留牀位。

sentences.english: Users of the carpark need to pay fees set by the operator.
sentences.chinese: 使用此停車場需繳付由營運商釐定的停車費。

sentences.english: Any subscription fee paid shall be non-refundable in all circumstances.
sentences.chinese: 已繳付之服務費概不發還，亦不能墊支其它費用。

sentences.english: Users of the lorry park need to pay fees as set by the operator.
sentences.chinese: 使用此停車場需繳付由營運商釐定的停車費。

definition: to return (sth borrowed etc)/to send back/to refund/to rebate
to transfer (money to a bank account)
